<br>
Level range: 25-40 ?<br>
<br>
Time Limit: I'd say, max 4-5 hours in one day. A week long event would fizzle out fast, imho. You probably wouldn't have enough people online all the time, and in my idea you'd have to have a monitor online for each team.<br>
<br>
What: Two teams would be created, let's call them Blue and Red for now. Everyone who wants to play would sign up on the website and be <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> assigned</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to a team. You might get on the same team as your buddy, and you might not. We'd have to make sure the teams were relatively even, so not everyone could be Blue just because they wanted to. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
We'd pick an interesting zone, perhaps change the zone everytime the event is scheduled and you would not be permitted to zone out. If you did, you would not be allowed to zone back in, perma-dead for the remainder of the event. Also, no going anonymous, roleplay would be acceptable but your team tag would have to remain visible at all times.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure how guildwars work, does anyone know if death messages are broadcast to the zone like in a duel? I personally think it would be fun to keep score and see who &quot;wins&quot; each event (most kills in the time period). We could also post kill records like VI does for the PvP RP server, that would be neat. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
We'd have to set rules regarding bind camping, otherwise I can't think of any other nonallowable tactics, it should be pretty much anything goes. Zones we choose would need to be melee bindable or next to a melee bindable zone (this would be the only acceptable zoning allowed).<br>
<br>
