<br>
I think doing something like counterstrike could work out well. Have a person designated the &quot;hostage.&quot; Bring the hostage to a certain part of the zone, and score points over time for however long they are there. You would have to bring the hostage by the follow command, so bards wouldn't have too much of an unfair advantage here, since the leader could be picked off with relative ease if alone. I don't know how many times I almost let group members die from going too fast while following me somewhere from NPC's. With PC's its much more dangerous since there's a lot more possible ways to kill you. Could also negate the bard speed by having the hostage be someone with JBoots or be able to SoW themselves. <br>
<br>
A different variant could be last man standing. All out war with the victor being whoever has more people standing after a certain time or a surviving player or players. Would have to rule out AE spells though, except for maybe buffs. A team full of magicians, wizards, and bards could easily knock out a team without sufficient resists, meaning everyone would twink out a few key classes just for the war. While it would be entertaining, doesn't make things entirely fair. Every class needs to be useful. Even with resists though, I'm sure a few support classes would be right there to finish off people who took damage from the AE's, leaving even those with good resists pretty much screwed and left without help.<br>
<br>
Could vary from war to war though. Just 2 scenarios that came off the top of my head. I dunno myself about ruling out certain spells, I guess it could vary with the number of classes on each team. I do like the idea of random teams though, makes for interesting play interaction and be able to learn a class from someone else, or learn something about your own you maybe didn't know.<br>
